Watts Water Technologies, Inc. Key Developments

Watts Water Technologies, Inc. Presents at KeyBanc Capital Markets Industrial, Automotive and Transportation Conference, Jun-01-2017 08:00 AM
May 19 17
Watts Water Technologies, Inc. Presents at KeyBanc Capital Markets Industrial, Automotive and Transportation Conference, Jun-01-2017 08:00 AM. Venue: InterContinental Hotel, 510 Atlantic Ave., Boston, Massachusetts, United States. Speakers: Robert J. Pagano, Chief Executive Officer, President and Director.


Watts Water Technologies, Inc. Increases Quarterly Dividend, Payable on June 16, 2017
May 9 17
Watts Water Technologies, Inc. announced an increase in its quarterly dividend of 5.5%, or $0.01, to $0.19 per share, on each outstanding share of the Company’s Class A and Class B Common Stock. The dividend will be paid on June 16, 2017, to stockholders of record at the close of business on June 2, 2017.


Watts Water Technologies, Inc. Announces Unaudited Consolidated Earnings Results for the First Quarter Ended April 2, 2017
May 4 17
Watts Water Technologies, Inc. announced unaudited consolidated earnings results for the first quarter ended April 2, 2017. For the quarter, the company reported net sales of $347.2 million against $344.2 million a year ago. Operating income was $35.7 million against $31.2 million a year ago. Income before income taxes was $30.8 million against $26.9 million a year ago. Net income was $21.7 million against $16.2 million a year ago. Basic and diluted net income per share was $0.63 against $0.47 a year ago. Net cash used in operating activities was $9.1 million against $21.9 million a year ago. Additions to property, plant and equipment was $5.8 million against $9.2 million a year ago. Operating income - as adjusted was $38.4 million against $37.3 million a year ago. Net income - as adjusted was $22.3 million against $19.6 million a year ago. Diluted earnings per share - as adjusted were $0.65 against $0.57 a year ago. Negative free cash outflow was $14.9 million against $31.0 million a year ago. Net debt was $336.6 million as on April 2, 2017.


