Watts Water In Action



Watts Brings Clean Water to Kids in the Philippines
Read More




A Long History
Watts Water Technologies, Inc. has a long history: The Company was founded by Joseph E. Watts in 1874 under the name Watts Regulator Company. Watts Regulator started as a small machine shop supplying parts to the New England textile mills, including manufacturing pressure-reducing and relief valves to ensure the safe operation of water heaters and boilers.
Breadth & Depth
Today Watts Water, through its subsidiaries, is a global provider of plumbing, heating, and water quality solutions for residential, industrial, municipal, and commercial settings.  Our family of companies offers one of the most varied plumbing, heating, and water quality product lines in the world. We offer a wide range of world-class, water-related solutions focused on:

Plumbing & Flow Control
Water Quality & Conditioning
Water Reuse & Drainage
HVAC
Municipal Waterworks

Global Presence
We have a global presence, from our corporate headquarters in North Andover, MA, to key business subsidiaries in the Americas, EMEA, and Asia-Pacific. In addition, the Watts Water Technologies, Inc. executive team brings together a significant depth and breadth of management experience.
Strategic Goals
Watts Water is traded on the New York Stock Exchange under the symbol  “WTS.”  As a public company, growing shareholder value is critical. To that end, we focus on a five-part Global Strategy: Growth, Commercial Excellence, Operational Excellence, “One Watts Water,” and a Talent & Performance Culture.

 





